  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd : \u0b85\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf \u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b9e\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Militants Attacking Civilians: Manifesting the Danger Signal",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "First the police and then the army were deployed for security duties to ensure security at petrol stations.",
        "Initially, the police followed the practice of arresting members of the public at gunpoint when they raised questions about irregularities in fuel supply.",
        "This not only caused strong criticism from all over the country but also created opposition among the people.",
        "The police have been advised to exercise some patience with the general public in such cases.",
        "After that, the police in some fuel filling stations brought the people they needed and did activities to get kerosene, petrol and diesel.",
        "This also irritated the soldiers stationed there. At the culmination of this, a traffic police officer was severely assaulted by an army soldier on security duty at a petrol filling station in Warakapola.",
        "Apart from all these, now the army has also started attacking the people seeking justice near the petrol filling stations.",
        "A video of an army officer kicking a youth is going viral on social media and the internet. But there is still no definite information about where it took place.",
        "Army soldiers take a young man by the hand and bring him to his superior. Immediately, the military officer there kicks the young man in the chest. He warns the young man who came to ask about it and tells him to leave.",
        "No one there had the courage to speak about the action of the military officer unless the police officer and other police officers who were watching this told the youth to disperse. Because there are more soldiers than police.",
        "In this way, the police and army coming together to attack the common people is going to have dangerous consequences.",
        "At some point there may be situations where the general public gets impatient and lays hands on the security forces. Is this what this government wants?",
        "The government knows very well that the general public does not engage in arguments at petrol stations in vain. All of them, waiting in queues for days, are denied fuel at the last moment.",
        "But fuel is stored at the filling station. The common people's grievances are that the police and the army are protecting these for those who need them. This cannot be denied.",
        "Even as the government announced to prioritize fuel supply to security and health sectors, there have been complaints that some police officers are buying excess petrol and diesels and selling them to outsiders at exorbitant rates.",
        "This includes some traders in the area and individuals who are friendly with the police. At the same time, the important thing is that even though the government has announced that they cannot distribute petrol and diesel in cans except kerosene, the police are liberally carrying it out.",
        "Police come in jeeps and take them away in cans. It is not known to whom they are being transported.",
        "Youngsters and family members who survive by driving autos every day get angry after seeing this. At the same time, corruptions have also increased in the matter of kerosene.",
        "But if you question this, the military and the police are now using repression.",
        "This cannot be taken for granted. A situation where the youth and the general public clash with the security forces can create tension across the country and risk spilling over into violence.",
        "The government should come to some conclusions about this immediately. Instead of that, there is no point in convening the parliament and talking about unnecessary issues."
      ],
